"%lld/%lld" = "%1$lld/%2$lld";
"Drop7.instructions" = "# Drop 7\n\nDrop numbered discs into a 7×7 grid and clear them with chain reactions.\n\n## How to play\n\n- **Tap a column** to drop the current disc — it falls to the lowest empty cell.\n- A disc with value **N** clears when **N contiguous discs** sit in its row or column (counting itself, including wrapped or cracked discs).\n- Cleared discs trigger gravity. Falling discs may form new matches — that's a **chain**.\n\n## Wrapped discs\n\n- **Gray (wrapped)** discs hide a number.\n- A wrapped disc next to an explosion **cracks**.\n- A cracked disc next to another explosion **reveals** its number, which can then chain.\n\n## Levels and scoring\n\n- Every level a new wrapped row pushes up from the bottom. Levels arrive faster as you progress.\n- Reaching a new level awards a **level bonus**.\n- **Clearing the entire board** awards a **70,000-point bonus**.\n- Long chains score *exponentially* more than simultaneous matches — set up cascades for big scores.\n\n## Game over\n\nThe game ends when a disc would be pushed off the top of the grid, or when no column has space for the next disc.";
